### Implementation Ambiguities (`draft-ietf-moq-transport`)
Alan Frindell shared feedback from trying to implement draft-18 of `draft-ietf-moq-transport`:
* **Ambiguity in Cancellation**: The draft currently introduces three overlapping methods to cancel or terminate bidirectional streams: sending `STOP_SENDING`, resetting the stream (`RESET_STREAM`), or finishing the stream (`FIN`). 
* It is unclear if they share identical semantics or if one is authoritative. Alan requested that WG members review and comment on the GitHub issues he filed to provide implementers with clear guidance.

